{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b1c299ec-bf13-4f67-a663-0bfa28981063","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"12b9e1fc-5793-4ced-992a-d57dee500746","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":154,"requestId":"0426:119996:1810BA4:1B6CA9C:69E82035"},"id":"24333a63-f46c-45ee-95bd-af197dadae0d","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:11:21.970Z","parentId":"74a37504-3f7e-4c24-9da7-631452cab530"}
